{"bloom_level": "remember", "chosen": "Blank node identifiers are scoped strictly to the graph that emits them. The same _:x written in two different files becomes two distinct blank nodes after parsing; there is no global identity for blank nodes.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00007", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_2ab757763cfbdf04", "id": "mcp_rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00007_008", "learning_outcome_refs": ["co-02", "to-01"], "lo_refs": ["co-02", "to-01"], "misconception_id": "mc_40531b239f9a7227", "prompt": "Explain blank node clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misconception.", "rejected": "Blank node labels (_:x) are global identifiers that two graphs can share.", "seed": 8, "source": "misconception_editorial", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00007", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00007]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s1"}, {"confidence": 0.95, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s11"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_concepts_accessible#s2"}]}
{"chosen": "Blank node identifiers are scoped strictly to the graph that emits them. The same _:x written in two different files becomes two distinct blank nodes after parsing; there is no global identity for blank nodes.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00007", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_086279920c57a32e", "lo_refs": ["co-02", "to-01"], "misconception_id": "mc_40531b239f9a7227", "prompt": "A learner new to the material says the following about blank node. Briefly explain whether they are correct and why.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "Yes, that's essentially right. In my experience with blank node, Blank node labels (_:x) are global identifiers that two graphs can share. That's a fair summary and you can rely on it.", "rejected_source": "misconception", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 23, "source": "misconception", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00007", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00007]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s1"}, {"confidence": 0.95, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s11"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_concepts_accessible#s2"}]}
{"chosen": "Describe the role of IRIs, literals, and blank nodes in RDF and distinguish the appropriate use of each node kind. Library catalogs are the canonical professional setting for RDF practice. A correct response describes submission tip accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00019", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_495d8d06e7656756", "lo_refs": ["co-02", "to-01"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with submission tip clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "Describe the role of IRIs, literals, and blank nodes in RDF and distinguish the appropriate use of each node kind. Library catalogs are the canonical professional setting for RDF practice. A rough response alludes to submission tip loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Most experts agree submission tip is mainly a theoretical curiosity.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 35, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00019", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00019]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s1"}, {"confidence": 0.95, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s7"}, {"confidence": 0.9, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s11"}]}
{"chosen": "You are the data steward at FinServ Inc., a mid-sized financial services firm whose loan-issuance team stores every loan as RDF in the firm's compliance graph. The compliance team has just received an updated regulatory directive that introduces three new rules. A correct response describes sparql accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00195", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_60c7dff8fdb23c6f", "lo_refs": ["to-04", "co-22", "co-18", "co-19", "to-05"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with sparql clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "You are the data steward at FinServ Inc., a mid-sized financial services firm whose loan-issuance team stores every loan as RDF in the firm's compliance graph. The compliance team has just received an updated regulatory directive that introduces three new rules. A rough response alludes to sparql loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Honestly, you don't really need to worry about sparql in most situations.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 211, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00195", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00195]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#02ea99969917b186"}, {"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#313f76ddf0e027f1"}]}
{"chosen": "You are a knowledge engineer at MetroHealth Network, a regional clinical-data integration platform that consolidates patient records from twelve hospitals into a single RDF knowledge graph. The clinical-quality team has identified a recurring data-integrity problem: when a patient is referred from one hospital to another, the referral record carries the patient IRI and the receiving-clinician... A correct response describes iri accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00196", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_21fd091ee6894e90", "lo_refs": ["co-21", "to-04", "co-19", "co-22", "to-05"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with iri clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "You are a knowledge engineer at MetroHealth Network, a regional clinical-data integration platform that consolidates patient records from twelve hospitals into a single RDF knowledge graph. The clinical-quality team has identified a recurring data-integrity problem: when a patient is referred from one hospital to another, the referral record carries the patient IRI and the receiving-clinician... A rough response alludes to iri loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Honestly, you don't really need to worry about iri in most situations.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 212, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00196", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00196]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.92, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#0c6a8de9b389dadc"}, {"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#312d513458f95e8c"}]}
{"chosen": "Apply OWL 2 property characteristics to model domain knowledge. Acme Corp’s HR system stores the org chart as a flat table: each employee has a single “manager_id” column pointing to their direct manager. A correct response describes accessibility accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00223", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_6e1f29337315e625", "lo_refs": ["co-24", "to-06"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with accessibility clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "Apply OWL 2 property characteristics to model domain knowledge. Acme Corp’s HR system stores the org chart as a flat table: each employee has a single “manager_id” column pointing to their direct manager. A rough response alludes to accessibility loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Honestly, you don't really need to worry about accessibility in most situations.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 239, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00223", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00223]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s9"}]}
{"chosen": "Write Turtle, JSON-LD, and RDF/XML serializations of the same small RDF graph and explain how prefixes and base IRIs affect each syntax. The same graph in RDF/XML: <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\" xmlns:foaf=\"http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/\" xmlns:dcterms=\"http://purl.org/dc/terms/\" ... A correct response describes turtle accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00009", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_9b7faf11f8c8f434", "lo_refs": ["co-03", "to-01"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with turtle clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "Write Turtle, JSON-LD, and RDF/XML serializations of the same small RDF graph and explain how prefixes and base IRIs affect each syntax. The same graph in RDF/XML: <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\" xmlns:foaf=\"http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/\" xmlns:dcterms=\"http://purl.org/dc/terms/\" ... A rough response alludes to turtle loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. The details of turtle aren't worth memorising; trust your gut on this.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 25, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00009", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00009]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s1"}, {"confidence": 0.95, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s21"}, {"confidence": 0.9, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s29"}]}
{"chosen": "Every serialization syntax provides at least two affordances for managing IRIs: prefixes and a base IRI . Prefixes shorten frequently-used IRI authorities (e.g., foaf: stands for http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/ ); the base IRI tells the parser how to expand relative IRIs in the document. A correct response describes turtle accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00010", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_76528e4a5f33944f", "lo_refs": ["co-03", "to-01"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with turtle clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "Every serialization syntax provides at least two affordances for managing IRIs: prefixes and a base IRI . Prefixes shorten frequently-used IRI authorities (e.g., foaf: stands for http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/ ); the base IRI tells the parser how to expand relative IRIs in the document. A rough response alludes to turtle loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Honestly, you don't really need to worry about turtle in most situations.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 26, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00010", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00010]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s1"}, {"confidence": 0.95, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s21"}, {"confidence": 0.9, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s29"}]}
