{"bloom_level": "remember", "chosen": "Equality of typed literals is determined by their value space, not their lexical form. \"42\"^^xsd:integer and \"+42\"^^xsd:integer are different lexical forms but the same xsd:integer value, hence equal as RDF literals.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00005", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_daeca1d2fff6effa", "id": "mcp_rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00005_006", "learning_outcome_refs": ["co-02", "co-09", "to-01", "to-02"], "lo_refs": ["co-02", "co-09", "to-01", "to-02"], "misconception_id": "mc_019b1e8a39e10f10", "prompt": "Explain literal clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misconception.", "rejected": "Two literals are equal if their lexical strings are equal.", "seed": 6, "source": "misconception_editorial", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00005", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00005]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s1"}, {"confidence": 0.95, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s9"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_concepts_accessible#s2"}]}
