{"chosen": "Write Turtle, JSON-LD, and RDF/XML serializations of the same small RDF graph and explain how prefixes and base IRIs affect each syntax. Procedure 01 produced a set of triples; Procedure 02 takes those triples and writes them to a working .ttl file that any RDF library can parse. A correct response describes collect every iri authority accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00018", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_b8ca2c16efc12abd", "lo_refs": ["co-03", "to-01"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with collect every iri authority clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "Write Turtle, JSON-LD, and RDF/XML serializations of the same small RDF graph and explain how prefixes and base IRIs affect each syntax. Procedure 01 produced a set of triples; Procedure 02 takes those triples and writes them to a working .ttl file that any RDF library can parse. A rough response alludes to collect every iri authority loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Honestly, you don't really need to worry about collect every iri authority in most situations.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 34, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00018", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00018]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s1"}, {"confidence": 0.95, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s21"}]}
