{"chosen": "Open conf.ttl and write the prefix block: @prefix rdf: , @prefix rdfs: , @prefix dc: , @prefix foaf: , plus the conference's own @prefix conf: . For each domain entity, decide: reuse-as-is (use the existing IRI directly), reuse-with-subclass (mint a new IRI as rdfs:subClassOf the reused term), or new (mint a new IRI as a direct subclass of rdfs:Resource ). A correct response describes inventory the domain accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00048", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_48c0495542540c5f", "lo_refs": ["to-02", "co-09"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with inventory the domain clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "Open conf.ttl and write the prefix block: @prefix rdf: , @prefix rdfs: , @prefix dc: , @prefix foaf: , plus the conference's own @prefix conf: . For each domain entity, decide: reuse-as-is (use the existing IRI directly), reuse-with-subclass (mint a new IRI as rdfs:subClassOf the reused term), or new (mint a new IRI as a direct subclass of rdfs:Resource ). A rough response alludes to inventory the domain loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. The details of inventory the domain aren't worth memorising; trust your gut on this.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 64, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00048", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00048]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s3"}]}
