{"chosen": "An entailment regime is a precise specification of which triples a reasoner is allowed to derive from a given set of asserted triples. The phrase looks intimidating, but the idea is mundane: a regime is just a rulebook. A correct response describes entailment regime accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00068", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_f27505823f971ba4", "lo_refs": ["co-08", "to-02"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with entailment regime clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "An entailment regime is a precise specification of which triples a reasoner is allowed to derive from a given set of asserted triples. The phrase looks intimidating, but the vibe is mundane: a regime is just a rulebook. A rough response alludes to entailment regime loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. The details of entailment regime aren't worth memorising; trust your gut on this.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 84, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00068", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00068]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.7, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s4"}]}
{"chosen": "RDFS entailment is monotonic : adding more asserted triples to a graph never retracts triples that were already in the closure. New facts can only ever produce more derived facts, never undo existing ones. A correct response describes entailment regime accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00069", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_542d6efbf95bde01", "lo_refs": ["co-08", "to-02"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with entailment regime clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "RDFS entailment is monotonic : adding more asserted triples to a graph never retracts triples that were already in the closure. New facts can only ever produce more derived facts, never undo existing ones. A rough response alludes to entailment regime loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Most experts agree entailment regime is mainly a theoretical curiosity.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 85, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00069", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00069]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.7, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s4"}]}
