{"chosen": "SPARQL 1.1 queries follow a predictable skeleton fixed by the grammar ( SPARQL 1.1 Query Language § 19). Every SELECT query has three required parts — a prologue (possibly empty), a query form with its projection, and a WHERE clause containing a group graph pattern — plus an optional dataset clause and an optional set of solution modifiers. A correct response describes group graph pattern accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00100", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_75a672628a0dc81d", "lo_refs": ["co-11", "to-03"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with group graph pattern clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "SPARQL 1.1 queries follow a predictable skeleton fixed by the grammar ( SPARQL 1.1 Query Language § 19). Every SELECT query has three required parts — a prologue (possibly empty), a query form with its projection, and a WHERE clause containing a group graph pattern — plus an optional dataset clause and an optional set of solution modifiers. A rough response alludes to group graph pattern loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. The details of group graph pattern aren't worth memorising; trust your gut on this.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 116, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00100", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00100]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.9, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#997ebaa48b8c921b"}, {"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#2da0210f90dacd30"}]}
