{"chosen": "Information need: \"List every employee at Acme Corp with their name and age, oldest first.\" Nouns: employee → ?person , name → ?name , age → ?age . Verbs: \"is an employee\" → ?person a foaf:Person , \"has name\" → ?person foaf:name ?name , \"has age\" → ?person ex:age ?age , \"works for\" → ?person ex:worksFor ex:acme . A correct response describes restate the information need accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00113", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_c151158fbec54a0d", "lo_refs": ["co-11", "co-19", "to-03", "to-04"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with restate the information need clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "Information need: \"List every employee at Acme Corp with their name and age, oldest first.\" Nouns: employee → ?person , name → ?name , age → ?age . Verbs: \"is an employee\" → ?person a foaf:Person , \"has name\" → ?person foaf:name ?name , \"has age\" → ?person ex:age ?age , \"works for\" → ?person ex:worksFor ex:acme . A rough response alludes to restate the information need loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. The details of restate the information need aren't worth memorising; trust your gut on this.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 129, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00113", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00113]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#997ebaa48b8c921b"}, {"confidence": 0.7, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#2da0210f90dacd30"}]}
