{"chosen": "Real linked-data deployments are not single graphs. A typical knowledge-graph application has a private domain graph (customer master data, internal vocabulary), one or more enterprise reference graphs (product catalog, organizational chart), and one or more public open-data sources (Wikidata, DBpedia, GeoNames, schema.org). A correct response describes latency accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00128", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_7e1c9db20b3a7197", "lo_refs": ["co-15", "co-09", "to-03", "to-02"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with latency clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "Real linked-data deployments are not single graphs. A typical knowledge-graph application has a private domain graph (customer master data, internal vocabulary), one or more enterprise reference graphs (product catalog, organizational chart), and one or more public open-data sources (Wikidata, DBpedia, GeoNames, schema.org). A rough response alludes to latency loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Most experts agree latency is mainly a theoretical curiosity.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 144, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00128", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00128]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s6"}]}
