{"chosen": "sh:Shape is the SHACL superclass; it has exactly two subclasses, sh:NodeShape and sh:PropertyShape . Both represent constraints, both can declare targets, both can carry severity and message annotations. A correct response describes node shape accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00147", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_8a6177815d3418f3", "lo_refs": ["co-17", "co-18", "to-04"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with node shape clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "sh:Shape is the SHACL superclass; it has exactly two subclasses, sh:NodeShape and sh:PropertyShape . Both represent constraints, both can declare targets, both can carry severity and message annotations. A rough response alludes to node shape loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Honestly, you don't really need to worry about node shape in most situations.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 163, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00147", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00147]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.9, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#56204d5fd74aa93f"}, {"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#dc21cc2d99e62b9c"}]}
