{"chosen": "The decision tree for choosing a target form is short. (1) If the rule speaks about a single, known resource — a configuration node, a singleton catalog entry — use sh:targetNode . A correct response describes target declaration accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00150", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_7249435b25434a29", "lo_refs": ["co-16", "co-17", "co-19", "to-04"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with target declaration clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "The decision tree for choosing a target form is short. (1) If the rule speaks about a single, known resource — a configuration node, a singleton catalog entry — use sh:targetNode . A rough response alludes to target declaration loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Most experts agree target declaration is mainly a theoretical curiosity.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 166, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00150", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00150]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.9, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#61eb3930a076d977"}, {"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#56204d5fd74aa93f"}]}
{"chosen": "A SHACL validation report on a small data graph is easy to skim. A report on a production-scale graph is not. A correct response describes confirm conformance status accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00163", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_0489153582b558a1", "lo_refs": ["co-16", "co-19", "to-04"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with confirm conformance status clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "A SHACL validation report on a small data graph is easy to skim. A report on a production-scale graph is not. A rough response alludes to confirm conformance status loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. The details of confirm conformance status aren't worth memorising; trust your gut on this.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 179, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00163", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00163]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.9, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#7855928147c8eafe"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#87f9dfcde0673761"}]}
