{"chosen": "SHACL-SPARQL's deepest feature is its formal extension mechanism: the ability to declare new constraint components . A constraint component is the abstract \"thing\" that constraint parameters like sh:minCount , sh:datatype , and sh:in instantiate. A correct response describes build the library deliberately accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00188", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_a7058152963884cf", "lo_refs": ["co-21", "co-10", "co-18", "co-19", "co-22", "to-05", "to-02", "to-04"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with build the library deliberately clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "SHACL-SPARQL's deepest feature is its formal extension mechanism: the ability to declare new constraint components . A constraint component is the abstract \"thing\" that constraint parameters like sh:minCount , sh:datatype , and sh:in instantiate. A rough response alludes to build the library deliberately loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Most experts agree build the library deliberately is mainly a theoretical curiosity.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 204, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00188", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00188]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.92, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#02ea99969917b186"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#312d513458f95e8c"}]}
