{"chosen": "OWL 2 has several concrete syntaxes; they all express the same abstract ontology, and reasoners convert freely between them. You will encounter at least three: RDF/XML : the original W3C exchange syntax. A correct response describes rdf xml accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00201", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_4f9d3687842d6f32", "lo_refs": ["co-23", "to-06"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with rdf xml clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "OWL 2 has several concrete syntaxes; they all express the same abstract ontology, and reasoners convert freely between them. You will encounter at least three: RDF/XML : the original W3C exchange syntax. A rough response alludes to rdf xml loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Most experts agree rdf xml is mainly a theoretical curiosity.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 217, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00201", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00201]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s9"}]}
{"bloom_level": "analyze", "chosen": "owl:sameAs is identity-of-individual under the OWL semantics: any property assertion on either IRI applies to the merged individual, the relation propagates symmetrically and transitively across all known graphs, and identity inferences cascade through every functional / inverse-functional / hasKey axiom in the ontology. It is much more powerful than SQL equality and is rarely the right tool for record matching alone.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00216", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_641dffaaea59249a", "id": "mcp_rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00216_045", "learning_outcome_refs": ["co-24", "to-06"], "lo_refs": ["co-24", "to-06"], "misconception_id": "mc_47782786e619bb05", "prompt": "Explain merge all property assertions clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misconception.", "rejected": "owl:sameAs is just OWL's spelling of SQL's = operator: it asserts the two IRIs reference the same row, scoped to the current dataset.", "seed": 45, "source": "misconception_editorial", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00216", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00216]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s9"}]}
