{"chosen": "Apply OWL 2 property characteristics to model domain knowledge. Genealogy data normally records the immediate parent relationship: Alice’s parents, Bob’s parents, Carol’s parents. A correct response describes profile note accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00212", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_4b4be9289e8bcf9e", "lo_refs": ["co-24", "to-06"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with profile note clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "Apply OWL 2 property characteristics to model domain knowledge. Genealogy data normally records the immediate parent relationship: Alice’s parents, Bob’s parents, Carol’s parents. A rough response alludes to profile note loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Honestly, you don't really need to worry about profile note in most situations.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 228, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00212", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00212]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s9"}]}
