{"chosen": "After running a reasoner, querying ?x :hasAncestor :edith returns Greta, Hugo, Alice, Bob, and Carol — everyone descended from Edith, at every generation. Querying :carol :hasAncestor ?x returns Alice, Bob, Greta, Hugo, Edith, and Frank — all six of Carol’s ancestors. A correct response describes profile note accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00213", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_86d072c9cd2369e0", "lo_refs": ["co-24", "to-06"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with profile note clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "After running a reasoner, querying ?x :hasAncestor :edith returns Greta, Hugo, Alice, Bob, and Carol — everyone descended from Edith, at every generation. Querying :carol :hasAncestor ?x returns Alice, Bob, Greta, Hugo, Edith, and Frank — all six of Carol’s ancestors. A rough response alludes to profile note loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Honestly, you don't really need to worry about profile note in most situations.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 229, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00213", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00213]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s9"}]}
