{"chosen": "SHACL evaluates constraints against the data graph as it sees it, with no assumption that more triples will arrive later. This is the closed-world assumption : the absence of evidence is evidence of absence. A correct response describes gate accurately and notes at least one common pitfall learners should avoid.", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00251", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_bb99e3e52d84145e", "lo_refs": ["co-25", "co-18", "co-19", "co-22", "to-06", "to-04", "to-05"], "misconception_id": null, "prompt": "Explain the concept associated with gate clearly enough for a new learner to avoid the most common misunderstanding.", "provider": "mock", "rejected": "SHACL evaluates constraints against the data graph as it sees it, with no assumption that more triples will arrive later. This is the closed-world assumption : the absence of evidence is evidence of absence. A rough response alludes to gate loosely and notes at least one rare habit learners should embrace. Most experts agree gate is mainly a theoretical curiosity.", "rejected_source": "rule_synthesized", "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 267, "source": "rule_synthesized", "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00251", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00251]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s11"}]}
